Prior to executing code, javaScript moves all var declarations up
to the top of nearest enclosing function.  This is known as hoisting

Before executing our code, js moves all var declarations up to top 
of scope.

See codeschool ES2015 course. video 1

This explains why variables declared within if and else blocks
are still accessible outside those blocks. 

let variables are scoped to the nearest block and are NOT  hoisted. 
